We need some help figuring out the resolution for our lamprey encoders on our wheels. When we manually turn the wheels, we read about 2700 ticks per rot for 3 of our encoders and about 4000 for the other encoder using .getValue();
The lampreys came pre-assembled on the PG motor from the andymark swerve and steer module, which is discontinued.
the resolution is not stated in the specifications, and we are not sure how to get it with code.
without the exact resolution, our turn accuracy is not good. any ideas and solutions are welcomed.
